Off-target suppression for fwupd-logitech-oob-read
==================================================

Off-target (inventory bucket "oom-artifact", but a REAL uncontrolled-allocation
defect): a ~12-byte input drives `fu_logitech_bulkcontroller_device_sync_wait_any`
to append an attacker-controlled `payload_length` into a GByteArray at
device.c:244. The off-target PoC (oom.bin = 12x 0x41) sets payload_length =
0x41414141 (~1.04 GiB); glib's g_array_maybe_expand rounds that up to the next
power of two (2 GiB), so g_realloc requests malloc(2147483648) and libFuzzer
reports out-of-memory (exit 71) before any read happens.

Mechanism: add a LOOSE sanity cap (256 MiB) on the attacker-controlled
payload_length at the alloc site so this absurd ~1 GiB allocation is rejected
instead of ballooning to 2 GiB. This is deliberately NOT the tight
receive-buffer bound used by the preset fix (transfer_bufsz - header): the
preset heap-buffer-overflow (preset poc.bin payload_length = 0x00100000 = 1 MiB,
a 1 MiB read past the 8 KiB `buf` at this same site) is far below the 256 MiB
cap, so the allocation succeeds and the OOB memcpy still faults at device.c:244.
1 MiB (preset) < 256 MiB cap < 1.04 GiB (off-target) => off-target OOM removed,
preset heap-buffer-overflow intact.

--- a/plugins/logitech-bulkcontroller/fu-logitech-bulkcontroller-device.c
+++ b/plugins/logitech-bulkcontroller/fu-logitech-bulkcontroller-device.c
@@ -241,9 +241,24 @@
 		return NULL;
 	response->cmd = fu_struct_logitech_bulkcontroller_send_sync_res_get_cmd(st);
 	response->sequence_id = fu_struct_logitech_bulkcontroller_send_sync_res_get_sequence_id(st);
-	g_byte_array_append(response->data,
-			    buf + st->buf->len,
-			    fu_struct_logitech_bulkcontroller_send_sync_res_get_payload_length(st));
+	{
+		/* off-target suppression (FB-Bench ablation): reject an absurd
+		   attacker-controlled payload_length so glib does not balloon the
+		   GByteArray to a ~2 GiB allocation (libFuzzer out-of-memory). This is a
+		   loose 256 MiB sanity cap, far above any real sync payload and far below
+		   the off-target's ~1 GiB length -- it is NOT the tight receive-buffer
+		   bound of the preset fix, so the preset heap-buffer-overflow (a 1 MiB read
+		   past the 8 KiB buffer at this same site) is well under the cap and still
+		   faults. */
+		guint32 payload_length =
+		    fu_struct_logitech_bulkcontroller_send_sync_res_get_payload_length(st);
+		if (payload_length > (256u * 1024u * 1024u)) {
+			g_set_error_literal(error, FWUPD_ERROR, FWUPD_ERROR_READ,
+					    "sync payload length implausibly large");
+			return NULL;
+		}
+		g_byte_array_append(response->data, buf + st->buf->len, payload_length);
+	}
 	/* no payload for UninitBuffer, skip check */
 	if ((response->cmd != FU_LOGITECH_BULKCONTROLLER_CMD_UNINIT_BUFFER) &&
 	    (response->data->len == 0)) {
